1. Open PowerShell.

2. Copy and paste the command below into PowerShell, and press Enter.

 Get-ExecutionPolicy -List

3. You will now see all execution policies. The policies are listed in precedence order.

4. Open Settings, and click/tap on the Update & security icon.

5. Click/tap on For developers on the left side, check the Change execution policy to allow 
local PowerShell scripts to run without signing. Require signing for remote scripts. box under PowerShell on the right side, and click/tap on the Apply button.
